<P />






				<br clear="all"><br>

				<div class="title"><b><A NAME="3">BANFF'S GRAND HOTELS</A></b></div><br>

					<img src="http://www.moguls.com/images/nl/250_BSHext_winter.jpg" alt="Banff's Grand Hotels " border="1" align="right">





















	I have to admit, I am a little biased when it comes to staying in Banff. Two hotels stand head and shoulders above the rest, the Banff Springs Hotel and the Chateau Lake Louise. Built in 1888, the Banff Springs Hotel is steeped in history. The massive stone building reminds one of a grand castle. No stay here is complete without a visit to the spa and it's Hungarian mineral baths. The Chateau Lake Louise is the sister hotel of the Banff Springs. Seated on the shores of Lake Louise, the Chateau enjoys one of the most stunning backdrops of any hotel in North America.  Originally built in 1890, a series of renovations led up to 1982 when a major renovation and upgrade created the Chateau as we know it today.
<P>
These two hotels share a rich history and a tradition of excellent service, superior accommodations, succulent dining and unparalleled beauty.
<P>
What is the ideal Banff ski vacation? A split trip with nights at both hotels! Check out Moguls' exclusive Classic Canadian Snofari.
<P>
<a href='http://moguls.com/ski/nl_CanadianSnofari' target='_blank' style='color : #ffffcc; text-decoration : underline; font-weight : bold'>http://moguls.com/ski/nl_CanadianSnofari</a>

